Speaker: Tim Hoffmann Track:PyConDE As hard as we try to write good code, there will always be cases in which we wish we had designed a different function signature, chosen another attribute name, ... But you can't change it anymore because it's public API - or can you? Recorded at the PyConDE & PyData Berlin 2019 conference. https://pycon.de More details at the conference page: https://de.pycon.org/program/QXB8DR Twitter: https://twitter.com/pydataberlin Twitter: https://twitter.com/pyconde
